This article is pretty ok, but some examples given struck me as a little weird.<p>Example for "live()":
var newDiv = document.createElement('div');
newDiv.appendChild(document.createTextNode('hello, world!'));
[...]
document.body.appendChild(newDiv);<p>jQuery simplifies DOM elements creation and insertion:
var newDiv = $('<div>hello, world!</div>').appendTo('body');<p>It is kind of funny to see plain old DOM createElement/createTextNode in article about intricacies of jQuery. All of DOM elements creation in article uses non-jQuery mechanisms. Only one commenter mentioned that jQuery support easy elements creation/insertion. That way, article promotes somewhat half-baked usage of jQuery.
